This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with scheduling transmissions in a multihop wireless network. It could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it proposes a distributed node scheduling algorithm. Information Theory (cs.IT) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses load balancing and delay optimization. The paper also deals with system optimization, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses simulations to compare the proposed algorithm with other scheduling algorithms, which could place it in the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category.
